At least one of your mods is incompatible with the version of the game you're trying to run. You're also trying to use the DLCs but the first one was released with 1.4.1 so it will definitely not work with 1.3.1.

@Danny ShadowFox You should learn to troubleshoot this yourself. To be honest I don't think anyone here has the time hunt through this mess to tell you exactly which mods are installed incorrectly. Open the output_log.txt file and search for the string Exception. This takes you to problems like this: 

AssemblyLoader: Exception loading 'Kopernicus': System.Reflection.ReflectionTypeLoadException: The classes in the module cannot be loaded.

A message like that means Kopernicus didn't load, probably due to the wrong version of the mod for your version of KSP. You also get this for ResearchBodies, InfernalRobotics, SCANsat.Unity. But these aren't the only problems mods.

Just searching for the string Exception there are hundreds of hits in the output_log file. The message tells you what throws the exception. I would guess almost everyone of them is due to incorrectly installed mods. When KSP finally crashes it's compiling parts from KAS that are installed in the wrong directory path.

If you cannot figure out which version or how to correctly install mods, I would suggest using CKAN to install your mods.

@Danny ShadowFox FYI, every time you change something about your installation you need to upload new logs. Your old logs won't have useful information when you make changes to your installation.

Based on your original logs I would recommend uninstalling everything or copy the installation to a backup directory in you want to save something. Start with a clean install of the game only and see if that works. Once you have a working game install only then try installing mods. I still recommend using CKAN for mods as it will help avoid installing the wrong version or incompatible mods.

If all you did was update KSP to 1.4.5 I wouldn't expect things to work any better than last time. From your original logs it look like you installed the Making History and Breaking Ground Expansions. These DLC packs have different releases that only work with a specific version of the base game. You should start with the latest of all three: KSP 1.7.2, BG 1.1.0 and MH 1.7.1
